<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1803" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1802" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Cephalcia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cephalcia arvensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arvensis">Cephalcia arvensis</taxonomicName>
Panzer, 1802: vol. 86 pl. 9. ♀. Syntypes. Type locality: Germany [according to title of work]. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2254.1.1" author="Blank, SM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 96" refId="B20" refString="Blank, SM, Taeger, A, Liston, AD, Smith, DR, Rasnitsyn, AP, Shinohara, A, Heidemaa, M, Viitasaari, M, 2009. Studies toward a World Catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera). Zootaxa 2254 (1): 1 - 96, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2254.1.1" title="Studies toward a World Catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2254.1.1" volume="2254" year="2009">Blank et al. (2009)</bibRefCitation>
; Nomen protectum with respect to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Psen" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Psen lucorum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucorum">Psen lucorum</taxonomicName>
Schrank, 1802, nomen oblitum.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1803" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1803" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Cephalcia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cephalcia abietis subsp. var. var. intermedia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="abietis" subSpecies="var." variety="intermedia">Cephalcia abietis var. intermedia</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hellén">Hellen</normalizedToken>
, 1948: 40-41. ♀. Syntypes. Type locality: Russia, Karelia, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paanajärvi">Paanajaervi</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1803" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1803" baseAuthorityName="Hellen" baseAuthorityYear="1948" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Cephalcia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cephalcia intermedia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">Cephalcia intermedia</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Vikberg, V" journalOrPublisher="Notulae Entomologicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="61 - 65" refId="B190" refString="Vikberg, V, 1982. Notes on the taxonomy and the nomenclature of some mainly Fennoscandian sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Notulae Entomologicae 62 (2): 61 - 65" title="Notes on the taxonomy and the nomenclature of some mainly Fennoscandian sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta)." volume="62" year="1982">Vikberg (1982)</bibRefCitation>
; raised to species rank. 
<bibRefCitation author="van Achterberg, C" journalOrPublisher="Zooelogische Verhandelingen" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 98" refId="B180" refString="van Achterberg, C, van Aartsen, B, 1986. The European Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera: Symphyta), with special reference to the Netherlands. Zooelogische Verhandelingen 234: 1 - 98" title="The European Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera: Symphyta), with special reference to the Netherlands." volume="234" year="1986">Van Achterberg and van Aartsen (1986)</bibRefCitation>
; synonymy with 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. lariciphila" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="lariciphila">C. lariciphila</taxonomicName>
(Wachtl, 1898). syn. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authority="Panzer, 1803" authorityName="Panzer" authorityYear="1803" baseAuthorityName="Hellen" baseAuthorityYear="1948" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Cephalcia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cephalcia intermedia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Cephalcia intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has in recent years mostly been understood as a distinct species close to 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. arvensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Viitasaari, M" editor="Viitasaari, M" journalOrPublisher="A review of the suborder, the Western Palaearctic taxa of Xyeloidea and Pamphilioidea. Tremex, Helsinki" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="235 - 358" refId="B187" refString="Viitasaari, M, 2002b. The Northern European taxa of Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera). In: Viitasaari, M, Ed., Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. A review of the suborder, the Western Palaearctic taxa of Xyeloidea and Pamphilioidea. Tremex, Helsinki: 235 - 358" title="The Northern European taxa of Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera)." volumeTitle="Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I." year="2002 b">Viitasaari 2002b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Taeger, A" editor="Blank, SM" journalOrPublisher="Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="399 - 504" refId="B172" refString="Taeger, A, Blank, SM, Liston, AD, 2006. European Sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) - A Species Checklist for the Countries. In: Blank, SM, Schmidt, S, Taeger, A, Eds., Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects. Goecke and Evers, Keltern: 399 - 504" title="European Sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) - A Species Checklist for the Countries." volumeTitle="Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects." year="2006">Taeger et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
), but with more extensively dark-patterned adults, occurring in northern Europe and the central European mountains. Because of its dark coloration, specimens of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. intermedia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also be mixed up with 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. lariciphila" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="lariciphila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. lariciphila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Wachtl, 1898), but the host plant of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. intermedia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Picea" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Picea" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Picea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as in 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. arvensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Pinaceae" genus="Larix" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Larix" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Larix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as in 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. lariciphila" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="lariciphila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. lariciphila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The status of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. intermedia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the supposed differences to 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. arvensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were discussed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vikberg, V" journalOrPublisher="Notulae Entomologicae" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="61 - 65" refId="B190" refString="Vikberg, V, 1982. Notes on the taxonomy and the nomenclature of some mainly Fennoscandian sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Notulae Entomologicae 62 (2): 61 - 65" title="Notes on the taxonomy and the nomenclature of some mainly Fennoscandian sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta)." volume="62" year="1982">Vikberg (1982)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A" journalOrPublisher="Entomologist's Gazette" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="161 - 164" refId="B164" refString="Shinohara, A, 1985. Some records of European Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera). Entomologist's Gazette 36 (2): 161 - 164" title="Some records of European Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera)." volume="36" year="1985">Shinohara (1985)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Midtgaard, F" journalOrPublisher="B: Norwegian Journal of Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="125 - 130" refId="B130" refString="Midtgaard, F, 1987. The Norwegian Xyelidae and Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera). Fauna Norvegica, Ser. B: Norwegian Journal of Entomology 34 (2): 125 - 130" title="The Norwegian Xyelidae and Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera). Fauna Norvegica, Ser." volume="34" year="1987">Midtgaard (1987)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Viitasaari, M" editor="Viitasaari, M" journalOrPublisher="A review of the suborder, the Western Palaearctic taxa of Xyeloidea and Pamphilioidea. Tremex, Helsinki" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="235 - 358" refId="B187" refString="Viitasaari, M, 2002b. The Northern European taxa of Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera). In: Viitasaari, M, Ed., Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. A review of the suborder, the Western Palaearctic taxa of Xyeloidea and Pamphilioidea. Tremex, Helsinki: 235 - 358" title="The Northern European taxa of Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera)." volumeTitle="Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I." year="2002 b">Viitasaari (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
. The only differences between 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. arvensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. intermedia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are in coloration: mainly of the abdomen, and less so of the antennae and legs. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A" journalOrPublisher="Entomologist's Gazette" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="161 - 164" refId="B164" refString="Shinohara, A, 1985. Some records of European Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera). Entomologist's Gazette 36 (2): 161 - 164" title="Some records of European Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera)." volume="36" year="1985">Shinohara (1985)</bibRefCitation>
pointed out that an unbroken range of color variability occurs between pale 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. arvensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the dark specimens identified as 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. intermedia." order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="intermedia.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. intermedia.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
This is in accordance with our observations, as the amount of dark color on the male abdomen varies considerably even in a single locality (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Cephalcia arvensis Panzer, 1802. Variability in colour pattern, dorsal habitus. A-D. Males (ZMUO. 032092, ZMUO. 033004, ZMUO. 030747, GP. 108460). E, F. Females (ZMUO. 040720, GP. 108471)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.84080.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/719517" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">6</figureCitation>
). Small differences in colouration of larvae are possibly not constant, as the larvae of 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. intermedia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
used for comparison were offspring of a single female. At present, there seems to be no convincing evidence for treating 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. intermedia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a species distinct from 
<taxonomicName family="Cimbicidae" genus="C." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. arvensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="arvensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">C. arvensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and we therefore synonymize them.
</paragraph>
